When you're dealing with a selfish narcissist or a con artist,
the old joke about how &quot;no good deed goes unpunished&quot;
seems to apply.

Rog's advice about being a better person is good, although
an ex who is a toxic narcissistic con artist will see
every bit of niceness as an opportunity to attempt
guilt trips, manipulation or worse.

If you didn't have kids together I'd recommend
completely cutting off absolutely all contact.

As it is the con artist knows she has you by the tail
and will abuse that situation.

If you are in a &quot;one party&quot; state for telephone recording
I would advise you to record all phone calls
between you and this con artist.

Over time you will be able to document her
attempts at giving you a guilt trip or conning you.
If you can prove this manipulative crap you might
be able to get the court to order her into some
kind of psychotherapy or at least a psych eval
to look this over regarding custody.

Have you tried &quot;I'm not calling for you to try
to give me some guilt trip or for you to try to
con me out of more money.  I'm calling
about the kids, not you.&quot;

If this woman is so manipulative, have you
wondered what effect this will have on the kids?
Won't her &quot;con artist&quot; or manipulative side
make the kids a little psychologically &quot;bent&quot;?
