First, have you told her your expecations regarding your
interactions?  For example,

1.  you will not come to each others homes but will rather meet on
neutral ground (i.e. a park where the kids can play, a place where you
can dine or a movie)

2.  you will not bail her out money wise - what she gets is all she
will get, she needs to budget and basically 'grow up and be held
accountable for her decisions as well as indecisions).

3.  her relationships are her business - and as such, you do not want
to be her best new friend and hear about it everytime you get
together.  If her relationships blow up, that is for her to handle -
not you.  You are again, NOT her new best buddy and that line needs to
be kept.

4.  if she cannot get and keep her life in order, financially and
emotionally, you do not feel she should have custody (does she?) - in
the event she continually finds herself in dire straits you will take
action to gain custody - (take a 'no prisoners approach).

Look its simple - the divorce means she goes to her corner and you go
to yours and she stay there.  Not continually drag you back to save
her from herself.  If she has the kids, this means the courts for some
reason feel she is the better parent, so do not bail her out, do not
save her butt because she's apparently not the better parent if you
have to keep doing this.  Then you do what needs to be done - not for
you and not for her but for the kids.  Regardless of what the kids
want - they are children, they have no idea what is best for them -
and they will recover.  But can they recover from being constantly
broke or at odds with money?

This is not about love, its about children - and an adult that
apparently cannot comply with the law and tend to her children.  Think
about this legally for once okay - take out the emotions.  I wish I
had.

About the arguing - question - why?  Are you married?  Does this
person have any real decision making authority in your life? Then why
allow it?  Don't want to hurt her feelings?  Did she think about
yours?  Feelings - they really mess up what needs to be done.

As mean as I sound, just trust me - take out the emotion, write it all
down - think it over - and tell her, on no uncertain terms that your
wallet is closed for business.  She gets sufficient support - make it
last or hand the kids over.

peace out
deb.
