Do what is within reason..... actually.

In the end of the custodial parent cannot get their act together, WHY
should you help them?  Really - are you helping the kids?

It is very very different if the child misses the bus, and you take
them to school or if they are sick and you take them to the doctor
because the person just cannot break away - but it is totally
different to give someone extra funds because they overspent or under
budgeted.

But at the same time - a dicussion should be held about 'THEM' having
some type of backup in place for these emergencies.  That is the
responsibility that comes with custody. And in this I mean it should
not become a habit.

To me, I would of loved it if my ex just took my kids out to eat,
spent some time with them maybe flying kites, or going to a movie or
just being there to talk to them.  That is what both parents should be
doing actually.

well peace out - good luck
